description:
### Context

Model Relating Viscosity to moisture, protein, and ash contents in flour used in baking ice cream cones.

### Source

V.T. Huang, J.B. Lindamood, P.M.T. Hansen (1988). "Ice-Cream Cone Baking: Dependence of Baking Performance on Flour and Batter Viscosity," Food Hydrocolloids, Vol. 2, #6, pp. 451-466.

### Description 

Model Relating Viscosity to moisture, protein, and ash contents in flour used in baking ice cream cones.

#### Model: V = b0 + b1M + b2P + b3A

### Variable Names: 
codeNum    (code number, n=39)
moisture    (%)
protein     (%)
ash         (%)
viscosity   (degree MacMichale)
title: Baking Ice Cream Cones
